<br>
Given that, what do you think is the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> DPM</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> threshhold for an <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;adequate&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> use of mana?  Is 2 sufficient?  Or should one hold out for 3 or better?  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Why?</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
I conclude that 2 <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> DPM</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is adequate, otherwise casting most nukes is not worthwhile.  I also think 3 <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> DPM</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is too high a standard, as nukes would only be worthwhile if not resisted.<br>
<br>
Two other, much more complex questions, also interest me.  How could you analyze the effectiveness of the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Maliso</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> line, and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Modulating Rods</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, which essentially enable other people to do their job better?<br>
<br>
Despite some of the emotion in the referenced thread, I am not looking to bash anyone.<br>
