<br>
I was addressing people reading the thread, not Raz specifically, and it was partly my tendancy to elaborate anything I say with examples.  I was considering the hypothetical situation in which damage shields would be more closely comparable to nukes in terms of damage per mana.  What I was suggesting was that if you could chain cast cadeau on the main tank stacking each damage shield, you'd get the net result of a 330 point damage shield on the single tank.  IE, a ludicrously powerful damage shield.<br>
<br>
And sure, if you would like to log malosi contributions, be my guest, and feel free to share your work hehe..  The problem I see is that there are so many different mobs with different resists.  I go to the hole and get resists from greens right and left, but head over to velketors and even partial resists are few and far between.  Good luck, and I agree it would be possible to measure specific situations, but due to both the variance between mobs and the randomness of resist rates in general I suspect that you will need a rather large amount of data to be worthwhile.  While I would love to see data gathered, and would happily take part in analyzing it, right now I don't mind relying on my intuition for using resist debuffs.<br>
